Momonga didn't do shit with Albedo's creation other than changing it so she loves him. Y'all be acting like Albedo was created by him and not Tabula Smaragdina.
Is this heresy according to what Momonga had set? Absolutely - I won't argue with that. Is this heresy according to Albedo's original creator, Tabula Smaragdina? Not at all.

Y'all be salty when clearly this was basically what Albedo's CREATOR, Tabula Smaragdina, fully intended. This doujin portrays Albedo in an alternate timeline in which Momonga did not tamper with how her character is supposed to be. If you didn't read the LN, watch the anime, or even bothered to read her wiki page, it is made extremely clear that this is pretty much the original setting for Albedo. But of course, it is in the canon timeline that she is madly in love with Momonga. It should have been obvious that this Albedo fall more in line with Tabula Smaragdina than Momonga. So while YES this Albedo does not follow the post-isekai timeline, but it also is not possible to deny that this is more or less what Tabula Smaragdina intended to begin with before Momonga decided to tamper with what had been there.
